eators. In discussing the impact of Greek myth, Greek literature, and Greek philosophy on modern writers, the present essayists try to determine how alive Greek classical culture is today, how meaningful it is, and how it can be perpetuated. Through their presentations in these seven essays, the contributors prove that the tradition does not suffer from lack of able guardians. These studies in the interpretation of literature and thought afford stimulating evidence that the classical tradition is still alive in our modern age.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aComparative literaturexClassical and modern. 0aComparative literaturexModern and classical. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aDe Laura, David J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFreedman, Ralph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFriedman, Melvin J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHayman, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoudiez, Leon S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSullivan, J. P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWill, Frederic, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWill, Frederic, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781477300411423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781477300411/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK